<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1476" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1476">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/133.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1911</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The President of Nicaragua has to-day been authorized by the Assembly to
                            negotiate with American bankers, through the good offices of the United
                            States of America, a loan not exceeding $20,000,000 <pb facs="1188" n="1072" xml:id="pg_1072"/> American gold. The Assembly also
                            authorized the President to conclude, subject to ratification by the
                            present Assembly, such treaties and contracts as may be necessary to
                            secure the loan.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Northcott.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>